description:
Junior Pappa - Tros EP
(Including a Remix by The Clark Kents) 

01 - Tros (Original Mix)
02 - Brain (Original Mix)
03 - Take it Or Leave it (Original Mix)
04 - Take it Or Leave it (The Clark Kents Remix)

Catalog Ref : VM 017
Promo Date : Thursday 2 February 2017
Release Date : Friday, 24th February 2017

Written by Nikolaos Pappas
Produced by Fabrice Dayan
Mastered with love by Steve Mill in London
____________________________________________________________

Nikolaos Pappas, Aka Junior Pappa is not a new comer in the Greek Electronic scene.

Since the late 90’s, the Thessaloniki kid didn’t stop to play everywhere in the country, warming for big names, organising parties, and finally decides to run his own club “the Real Rock n’ Rolla. On the production side, nothing here is about sirtaki, but you sometimes can clearly recognize some of his spicy roots, combined to sweating Tech House. Known for his classic bootlegs from Celeda, Martin Landsky or Danny Tenaglia, Nikolas deliver here what he calls “Big Floor Fillers for hungry dancers”

Tros EP, is a 3 dancefloor tools, traducing a particular taste for syncoped basslines, and catchy beats without any complexity. Between salt & pepper, the Greek cook pretends nothing more, nothing less: Effectiveness. 

In the end you will find a Beasty Remix who introduces an upcoming & rising Acid House duo: The Clark Kents. Max & Stan are long time friends that are living in London & Paris. For their first release ever, they produced an alternative version from “Take it Or Leave it”, bringing on their particular taste for dirtiness and early Chicago House grooves. A name to have a close look at, as far their first EP is waiting in the kitchen, ready to be served hot.

At the moment, Tros EP could be the most wanted record in Greece.
Understand: This is made for big rooms.

Release date is planned on Friday 24th February 2017. 
Feedbacks Welcome, Until then: Play it Loud !

description:
PachangaStorm & Oliver Deuerling Feat Square One - Countdown
Voyeur Music 016

01 - Countdown (Original Mix)
02 - Countdown (Antony Toga Remix)
03 - Countdown (Limitless Remix)

Catalog Ref : VM 016
Promo Date : Thursday 20th October 2016
Release Date : Friday, 20th January 2017
Mastered with love by Steve Mill in London
________________________________________________________________

No need to introduce the Munich Tech House Masters Pachangastorm & Oliver Deuerling.
The experienced german producers srike back with a tribute to Ali Rasul from the almighty Hip Hop band Square One, with the track “Countdown”. The Original version is definitely made for big sweating rooms, and the release contains a dirty breakbeat vision by Antony Toga, and a catchy deep remix by Limitless.

Release date is planned on Friday 20th January 2017. Feedbacks Welcome.
Until then, Play it Loud !

description:
FEM & QUENTIN SCHNEIDER – Faces EP 
(Including Faces, Find Us, The Search + Antony Toga Remix & Acapella Tool) 

01 - Faces (Original Mix)
02 - Find Us (Original Mix)
03 - The Search (Original Mix)
04 - The Search (Antony Toga Remix)
05 - The Search (Acapella Tool)

Catalog Ref : VM 015
Promo Date : Thursday 20th October 2016
Release Date : Friday, 28th October 2016
Mastered with love by Steve Mill in London
________________________________________________________________________

The French hyperactives producers FEM & Quentin Schneider became in few years, promising spokespersons of the French electronic scene. After playing alongside masters such as Robert Hood, Michael Mayer, Kevin Saunderson, Carl Craig, Josh Wink, Stephan Bodzin, Gui Boratto, Gary Beck or Alan Fitzpatrick, they finally decided to perform together as one. 

In 2012 and 2013, after they won a french award as young talents for the Astropolis Festival, they started to play in most of the famous western french festivals like Astropolis, Panoramas and Transmusicales, and finally enters smaller legendary venues like Badaboum, 1988 Live Club, Iboat and finally in the french temple of electronic music : The Rex Club. 

In 2016 FEM & Quentin Schneider finally enter the rising Voyeur Music crew, and delivers “Faces EP”, a production betwenn deep house and techno, tainted of a sexy grooves. The pack contains “Faces”, “The Search”, and “Find Us”, and includes a massive remix from Solomun’s favorite secret producer : Antony Toga.

Already supported by monsieur Laurent Garnier himself, Faces EP sounds to be a massive anthem from the smallest electronic clubs to massive Festivals & bigger stages. Release date is planned on Friday 28th October. Feedbacks Welcome.

Until then, Play it Loud !

Juan - Ethnocity EP  
Voyeur Music 004

01 - Ethnocity (Original Mix)
 02 - Merua (Original Mix) 
03 - Merua (Percapella Dub)

Catalog Ref : VM 004
 Release Date : Monday, 29 June 2015
 ------------------------------------------------------------------

Juan is that young French Dj that shake big crowds with his so particular tribal & spiritual music. From his residencies in Paris at Shmn & Attrape Rêve Huge parties, he is the perfect one to play besides Ruede Hagelstein, Edu Imbernon or Rampa, to name a few.

Ethnocity, is his debut EP on Voyeur Music. 
It’s a Tribal-Ethnic Travel through percussions, African vibes and Deep moods. This so special ’Shamanic Deep House’ style, is a part of a long list of upcoming magical tracks, made especially for a spiritual journey. So, fasten your seatbelt, and enjoy the ride.

Out on Monday 29 June 2015 on every Digital Platforms.

------------------------------------------------------------------
